{"title":"Gallery: Tour of Flanders 2023","link":"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2023/04/gallery-tour-of-flanders-2023/","date":1680636985000,"content":"<figure><img src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Z9A_9101.jpg?width=1200\" alt=\"Gallery: Tour of Flanders 2023\" /></figure><p>The <a href=\"http://cyclingtips.com/tag/2023-Tour-of-Flanders\" target=\"_blank\">Tour of Flanders</a>, <em>De Ronde</em>, is consistently one of road cycling’s most important races — arguably <em>the</em> most important for the hordes of Belgian fans that turn out along the Flemish cobbled climbs each April.</p>\n<p>Belgian <a href=\"http://cyclingtips.com/tag/Lotte-Kopecky\" target=\"_blank\">Lotte Kopecky</a> delivered for the local crowd on Sunday, cementing herself as one of the great classics racers by riding solo to her second win at the event in as many years.</p>\n<p>Photographers <a href=\"http://cyclingtips.com/tag/gruber-images\" target=\"_blank\">Jered and Ashley Gruber</a> were on the ground in Flanders capturing the race.</p>\n<p><strong>Also read:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2023/03/gallery-gent-wevelgem-2023/\" target=\"_blank\">Gallery: Gent-Wevelgem 2023</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2023/03/strade-bianche-2023-in-pictures/\" target=\"_blank\">Strade Bianche 2023 in pictures</a></li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.cyclingtips.com/2023/03/la-tourist-race-photo-gallery-a-rare-rainy-day-in-southern-california/\" target=\"_blank\">LA Tourist Race photo gallery: A rare rainy day in Southern California</a></li>\n</ul>\n<figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Z9A_9755-1340x1120.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1120\" /><figcaption>Lotte Kopecky out front en route to a Flanders repeat. <span>(Photo: Gruber Images)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Z9B_9788-1340x840.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"840\" /><figcaption>(Photo: Gruber Images)</figcaption></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Z9B_0764-1340x1118.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1118\" /><figcaption>The curse of the rainbow jersey is alive and well for Annemiek van Vleuten. <span>(Photo: Gruber Images)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Z9B_0067-1340x1466.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1466\" /><figcaption>Fans of all ages love De Ronde. <span>(Photo: Gruber Images)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Z9A_8839-1340x1732.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1732\" /><figcaption>The peloton. <span>(Photo: Gruber Images)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Z9A_9101-1340x696.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"696\" /><figcaption>Windmill pictures have become almost obligatory for photographers at Flanders. <span>(Photo: Gruber Images)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Z9B_0565-1340x823.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"823\" /><figcaption>Eventual runner up Demi Vollering and fifth place finisher Kasia Niewiadoma battling it out. <span>(Photo: Gruber Images)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Z9A_9346-5-1340x893.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" /><figcaption>The flag of Flanders gives an important context clue in case you forgot where you were. <span>(Photo: Gruber Images)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Z9B_0948-1340x893.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"893\" /><figcaption>The monuments will drain every racer. <span>(Photo: Gruber Images)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Z9A_9279-1340x838.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"838\" /><figcaption>Positioning is paramount early in the race as the peloton navigates narrow roads. <span>(Photo: Gruber Images)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Q4A7661-2-1340x663.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"663\" /><figcaption>Silvia Persico follows Lotte Kopecky. <span>(Photo: Gruber Images)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n<figure>\n<p></p><figure><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://cdn.cyclingtips.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/04/Z9B_0709-1340x1188.jpg?width=730\" alt width=\"1340\" height=\"1188\" /><figcaption>Kopecky after winning her second Tour of Flanders. <span>(Photo: Gruber Images)</span></figcaption></figure></figure>\n</figure>","author":"Will Tracy","siteTitle":"CyclingTips","siteHash":"30feca30fb3902119bf2da6559e7337232527b61c9abe0a00f5d7543c6aa6c84","entryHash":"7544bd7197a5c284e1c57f1e1d59fdb758f6d34329195a903709f9088f4de04e","category":"Cycling"}